raw_data.title: Software Testing Engineer
raw_data.description: • Works with technical staff to understand problems with software and resolve them.  • Resolves customer complaints with software and responds to suggestions for improvements and enhancements.  • Performs process and/or data modeling in support of the planning and analysis efforts using both manual and automated tools.  • Responsible for testing and analysis of all elements of the software systems. • Responsible for the installation, configuration, and maintenance of testing tools.  • Recognizes and troubleshoots problems with server hardware and applications software. Establishes and documents standards and procedures for management review.

raw_data.title: Software Developer
raw_data.description: • Write Automate testing of API’s and REST APIs to demonstrate functioning code that meets the requirements • Write the templates for AWS/Azure infrastructure as a code using terraform to build staging and production environments • Use Splunk and other monitoring tools to support production infrastructure • Work on credit card Payment and money transfer system which involves and understanding customer’s requirements which develops and deploying into Cloud based infrastructure environment • Code Review, Quality Co-ordination, Release Management, and bug fixing • Translates design into software. • Review of test cases and Unit Testing, Integration testing • Involve in writing the JUnit cases using Mockito framework as part of TDD approach. • Work with PDMs in preparing Business Scenarios and updating the same in JIRA. • Create custom services, filters, configuring dynamic UI routing and directives • Interact with business team to determine the technical feasibility of business requirements in confluence wiki. • Implement the business logic and discover patterns in the data as per business requirements and confer with team members for validation on the required format. • Ensure the quality assurance of the software being developed by creating unit test cases and mocking classes for testing the workflows and UI components, respectively. • Perform code review through GitHub to improve the quality of software. • Work with different system owners for application integrations and data exchange

raw_data.title: Data Architect
raw_data.description: • Reviews data loaded into the data warehouse for accuracy.  • Responsible for the development, maintenance and support of analyzing data in an enterprise data warehouse system and corresponding data marts.  • Troubleshoots and tunes existing data warehouse applications.  • Conducts research into new data applications and determines viability for adoption. Assists in establishing development standards.  • Evaluates existing subject areas stored in the data warehouse. Incorporates existing subject areas into an enterprise model. Creates new or enhanced components of the data warehouse or data repository solutions.
